OL,6,F"Over the last year, there had been a
OL,7,Fnumber of staff changes at senior
OL,8,Flevel, including a new chief
OL,9,Fexecutive, new directors and a number
OL,10,Fof new non-executive directors.
OL,11,FAlthough there were the beginnings of
OL,12,Fchange and recovery, and recognition
OL,13,Fof present and past concerns, there
OL,14,Fhad not yet been sufficient time to
OL,15,Fdemonstrate progress and for leaders
OL,16,Fto show they were dealing with the
OL,17,Frisks, issues, and challenges in the
OL,18,Fservice and how to resolve them
OL,19,Feffectively. This particularly related
OL,20,Fto matters of staff safety,
OL,21,Funchallenged or hidden bullying
OL,22,Fcultures, and a fear of speaking up.
OL,23,FThroughout the organisation, not all
OL,24,Fleaders demonstrated they had the
OL,25,Fskills to be effective leaders and to
OL,26,Fprotect staff from discrimination."
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G7/14
