OL,6,F"We have zero tolerance, to racism,
OL,7,Fmisogyny, and all forms of
OL,8,Fdiscrimination. While we are
OL,9,Fencouraged more colleagues are feeling
OL,10,Fconfident to speak up, we want
OL,11,Feveryone to feel safe to do so and are
OL,12,Freorganising our Freedom to Speak up
OL,13,Fservices in consultation with our
OL,14,Ffreedom to speak up leads, staff
OL,15,Frepresentatives and trade unions to
OL,16,Fmake sure that it meets the needs of
OL,17,Fall colleagues and gives confidence to
OL,18,Fthem in raising their concerns. We
OL,19,Fhave been undertaking an internal
OL,20,Freview, learning from lived
OL,21,Fexperience, which will strengthen our
OL,22,Fmechanisms and outcomes in response to
OL,23,Fconcerns raised.
