OL,6,F"We fully recognise we have a lot to
OL,7,Fdo and know we have not yet been able
OL,8,Fto fix all the problems ` many long-
OL,9,Fstanding and built up over many years.
OL,10,FHowever, we have changed and continue
OL,11,Fto change, the way we respond to and
OL,12,Fapproach those problems. It is
OL,13,Freassuring that the CQC has recognised
OL,14,Fthat we were at the beginning of a
OL,15,Fmajor transformation programme when
OL,16,Fthey visited; there were the
OL,17,Fbeginnings of change and recovery, as
OL,18,Fwell as recognition of present and
OL,19,Fpast concerns, but there had not yet
OL,20,Fbeen sufficient time to test the new
OL,21,Fways of working or their impact."
